# CAREER DEVELOPMENT

Career development is how you manage your career. Whether you are looking at improving in your current job, or moving up with Linamar, planning your own career development will help you succeed. This includes learning new skills or gaining new knowledge through experiences, training, feedback, etc. By creating a personal career development plan, you can set goals and objectives for your own personal career growth.

Take a few minutes and share your goals for your career development.

Other:

- Kevin is doing a great job in managing Structures Information System team.
- I couldn't be happier with Kevin Young as a supervisor.  His manner and professionalism make it a pleasure to work here.
- This is an exciting time to work in the field of information systems and the people here are great to work with. This is a great place to work!

1. What would you like to achieve in the next year?

In the process of creating the `Structures Microsoft Fabric Medallion Workflow` process. We are using the `Maintenance oil consumption` report as a test case to understand and document this new data analytics process. When complete Structures business data will be located in a centralized data lake enabling previously impossible insights. This process will enable us to securely manage Power BI, dashboards, and Notebooks. It will also encompass automated data collection for the management, creation, and visibility of statistical process control graphs and charts previously in the domain of Minitab.

2. List all the learning and job experiences that will help you in meeting these goals

- Study **[Statistical Process Control](https://www.taylorfrancis.com/books/mono/10.4324/9781315160511/statistical-process-control-john-oakland-robert-oakland#:~:text=Subsequent%20editions%20retained%20the%20'took,modern%20statistical%20process%20control%20techniques.)** book by John Oakland.
- Study **[Process Capability Analysis Cp, Cpk, Pp, Ppk - A Guide](../research/a_l/data_science/spc/process_capability_analysis.md#next-08-short-term--long-term-process-behaviour)** book.
- Watch this **[Power BI training resource](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vg5bwxhM2vs&list=PLtCzYvIWNgJE-NsGuUXbjYyJgQMSOFp3A)** series.
- Study **[Design MICROSOFT FABRIC Data Project with Medallion Architecture | Lakehouse + Spark + Power BI](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qG65DUcSjws)**
- Watch **[Building Power BI semantic models with Direct Lake in Microsoft Fabric](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ACbBgCwTXSg)** video.
- Study Python Pandas library with **[Create dataframe using Python Dictionaries](https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_dictionaries.asp)** tutorial.
- Study **[Master Data Modeling in Power BI - Beginner to Pro Full Course](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=air7T8wCYkU)** to get and transform data using power query using the Kimball approach.

3. What would you like to achieve in the next 3 to 5 years?

Cordinate an effort to securely manage all types of Linamar business data to include data used in statistical process control in the Structures Microsoft Fabric Power BI enabled workspace. This effort is to include a way to securely manage and view Power BI dashboards, reports, and notebooks.

4. Additional Comments: This is a great place to work!
